The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Sunday, December 21, 2003  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	 Bengal have recalled seamer Sabir Ali, opener Amitava Chakraborty and also included left-arm spinner Murtaza Lodhgar in the squad for their final Ranji Trophy tie against Gujarat to be played in Ahmedabad from December 25.				 																																																	THE SQUAD: Devang Gandhi (captain), Nikhil Haldipur, Arindam Das, Amitava Chakraborty, Safi Ahmed, Sanjib Sanyal, Laxmi Ratan Shukla, Aniruddha Roy, Murtaza Lodhgar, Utpal Chatterjee, Sourashish Lahiri, Ranadeb Bose, Shib Sankar Paul, Sabir Ali.				 																																																	 Siliguri beat Malda 1-0 in the Konark Sheet state football league in Malda on Saturday. Partha Karmakar netted the winner in the Group A encounter.				 																																																	 Tollygunge Club  represented by S.N. Mukherjee, Gaurav Ghose, Shiv Mohan, Subhankar Ghose, Hasan Safwi and Shyamal Bhattacharya  finished runners-up in the national finals of the McDowells Signature club golf meet at the Jaypee Greens Golf Resort on Saturday, according to information received here. 				 																																																	 Jasjeet Singh played steady golf to win the strokeplay event in the Goodricke East India amateur golf championship with a score of two-under 142 at Royal Calcutta Golf Club.				 																																																	 Hasina Khatun has been named skipper of the Bengal womens team for the ninth road race cycling championship to be held from December 24 to 28 at Rajarhat.				 																																																	 Football legend P.K. Banerjee will be felicitated at a special programme  Sonar Pradip  at Rabindra Sadan on Tuesday. Among the dignitaries to be present on the occasion are Milkha Singh, Kapil Dev and Manna Dey.				 																																																	 The final of the fifth N.K. Sood Memorial open handicap snooker tournament will be held at the YMCA College branch on Sunday.				 																																																	 Vinod Kumar Sewa beat Sourav Sukul 6-4, 6-4 to win the mens singles title in the floodlit tennis meet at Saturday Club.				 																																																	 Subroto Bose was elected president, while Navin Bhatia was elected secretary of the South Club.				 																																																	SNOOKER: N.K. Sood memorial open handicap meet final at YMCA.				 																																																	GOLF: East India amateur meet at RCGC from 8 am.				 																																																	GENERAL: Inauguration of indoor badminton stadium at Park Circus Byayam Samity.				 																																																	SWIMMING: Long distance meet from Panihati to Ahiritola Ghat.
